Up to 90% of visible skin aging is due to sun exposure, a process known as photoaging. UV rays damage collagen and elastin, leading to wrinkles, sagging, and pigmentation issues.

To protect your skin:

Apply a broad-spectrum sunscreen with at least SPF 30 daily, even on cloudy days.

Reapply every two hours, especially after swimming or sweating.

Wear protective clothing, wide-brimmed hats, and UV-blocking sunglasses.
